.entry-header
2025 Festival Title Sponsor
Presented by
Sponsor the Arts in Temple Terrace
2024 Sponsorship Form
Our modest group of volunteers could not produce the Festival without the generous donations and sponsorships of friends and businesses of our community. Your sponsorship will be gratefully appreciated. All profits are directly invested in the future of art and culture.
Open our
Sponsorship Form
to see the benefits we offer depending on your level of sponsorship.
For more information regarding our projects and events, or if you have any questions please use the form below to contact Sharon Gaskin, our  VP of Fundraising.
Your Name (required)
Your Email (required)
Your Message
Δ
Donate Now!
Click the “Donate” button and make a one time gift to the Temple Terrace Arts Council, or select “Make this a monthly donation” to become a sustaining supporter of arts and culture in Temple Terrace and beyond.

applications

Contact
.entry-header
The Council meets the 2nd Tuesday of the month at 6:30 p.m. in the Omar K. Lightfoot Recreation Center 10901 N. 56th St., Temple Terrace, 33617. No special skills or talents are required to join the Council, other than a willingness to work with people in a positive manner, and serve to support the mission.
Mailing Address
: Post Office Box 291266, Temple Terrace, FL 33687
Leave a message for the Temple Terrace Arts Council by phone 813.988.ARTS (2787), visit us on

, or email us using this form.

About
.entry-header
The Temple Terrace Arts Council (Temple Terrace Community Arts Festival Incorporated), is a registered 501 (c) 3 nonprofit organization whose mission is to
bring arts and culture to the community and beyond.
The Council is staffed by 14-16 volunteers who are responsible for three main activities:
The
Temple Terrace Arts & Crafts Festival
, which is held the second weekend in November (since 1973),
Fundraisers such as
Art en Blanc
(since 2012), and
Public art projects
, which may include Fish on Fence, concrete yard art, totems, murals, street art, and awards to artists.
